Reasoning: The paper deals with the complexity of graph coloring problems, which is a topic in both discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of forbidden induced subgraphs to characterize the $k$-colorability of certain graph classes suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the study of paths and cycles in graphs is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
